This petition is for a second EU referendum to be called because voters were misled. It does not ask for minimum voting or turnout thresholds (see separate petition).

Examples of misleading campaigning by Vote Leave include:

1. £350m "sent" to EU per week - misleading;
2. That money will be spent on the NHS - not true / now retracted;
3. Immigration control claims false;
4. Iraq and Syria shown on a map of countries "set" to join - misleading.

See Treasury Select Committee report (27/05/16).
